                            <comment id="138274" author="jfc" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2016 23:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Incomplete and out of date.&lt;br/&gt;
~ jfc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46248" author="liwei" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 10:12:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2b0033cc-1202-11e2-a663-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2b0033cc-1202-11e2-a663-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was master with ZFS OSTs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41247" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 04:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;status update: there is no new occurrence over one month&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39902" author="yujian" created="Mon, 4 Jun 2012 04:29:13 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Any chances this was related too and a retest with fresh b2_1 would help?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The failure reported in this ticket occurred on Lustre b2_1 build &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_1/86&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_1/86&lt;/a&gt;, which is v2_1_2_RC2, and which has &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-969&quot; title=&quot;2.1 client stack overruns&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-969&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-969&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; reverted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue did not occur consistently. The recovery-small test 59 passed on another test session with the same distro/arch combination, test nodes and Lustre build:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d3b1917a-aa27-11e1-bd84-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d3b1917a-aa27-11e1-bd84-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39898" author="green" created="Mon, 4 Jun 2012 03:26:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hm, x86_64 vs i686 is a suspicious combination, we reverted lu969 recently (from b2_1) to fix some other errors for such a combination.&lt;br/&gt;
Any chances this was related too and a retest with fresh b2_1 would help?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39867" author="tappro" created="Sun, 3 Jun 2012 02:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please, don&apos;t do that. ORI-628 is about ZFS only, moreover if bug happens in master it must be LU- otherwise nobody will work on it thinking this is not master bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39800" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Fri, 1 Jun 2012 06:50:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there is no bug found in the logs, and this bug occurs mostly at Orion branch, this is the only one failed at 2.1.2 RC2,&lt;br/&gt;
and there is also a bug ORI-628 to track the same issue, it&apos;s better to duplicate this one as ORI-628, for it is more easy&lt;br/&gt;
to reproduce at Orion. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;btw, this bug seems only occur at x86_64 + i686 (server + client) architecture.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="39776" author="pjones" created="Thu, 31 May 2012 19:07:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hongchao&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
